      "id": "bug-010",
      "timestamp": "2026-07-19T00:00:00.000Z",
      "error_message": "PlatformException(DeviceControlCallException, Create Controller failed, null, null) - commissioning fails with code -2 at 'Controller setup' step",
      "file": "ios/Classes/Framework Helpers/DefaultsUtils.m, ios/Classes/DeviceControlHandle.m",
      "root_cause": "newDeviceControllerCall() calls [ZGMTRControllerFactory sharedInstance] startControllerOnExistingFabric:/startControllerOnNewFabric: but never checks that the factory was actually started. Startup happens once at plugin registration via InitializeZGMTR() (FlutterMatterPlugin.m), using the deprecated startup: API which only returns a bare BOOL with no error detail; if it silently fails (e.g. keychain access rejected after switching Xcode signing teams) both fabric-start calls return nil and the exception message gives no clue why.",
      "fix": "Added NSLog diagnostics in InitializeZGMTR() (factory startup failure, FabricKeys nil, both fabric-start calls nil) and a factory.isRunning check + isRunning value in the thrown exception reason in newDeviceControllerCall(), so the next run's native console reveals the real cause instead of a generic 'Create Controller failed'.",
      "tags": [
        "ios",
        "matter-controller",
        "keychain",
        "signing-team",
        "commissioning",
        "diagnostics"
      ],
      "related_bugs": [],
      "occurrences": 1,
      "last_seen": "2026-07-19T00:00:00.000Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "bug-011",
      "timestamp": "2026-07-19T00:00:00.000Z",
      "error_message": "pairDevice error Instance of 'CallPlatformException' - no detail, commissioning fails silently at Secure session step",
      "file": "lib/src/exception.dart",
      "root_cause": "CallPlatformException held a 'message' field (built as '[$code] Call $methodName params ... failed' in controller.dart _requestPlatform) but never overrode toString(), so any '$e' string interpolation (including CommissioningController._addLog('pairDevice error $e $s')) printed the default 'Instance of CallPlatformException' instead of the actual message/error code.",
      "fix": "Made CallPlatformException implement Exception and added toString() returning the message, so the real platform error code/method/params now show up in logs.",
      "tags": [
        "dart",
        "exception-handling",
        "commissioning",
