      "id": "bug-022",
      "timestamp": "2026-07-20T00:00:00.000Z",
      "error_message": "Wildcard subscribe (Info tab live feed: all endpoints/clusters/attributes/events) never delivers reports, while concrete-path subscribe (On/Off tab) works fine",
      "file": "ios/Classes/DeviceControlHandle.m, android/src/main/kotlin/com/tyx/flutter_matter/DeviceControl.kt",
      "root_cause": "ChipPathId.forWildcard() (Dart) encodes as {\"id\": -1, \"type\": \"wildcard\"}. Both native bridges read only the \"id\" field when building attribute/event paths for subscribe and read, ignoring \"type\" entirely, so a wildcard request got built as a concrete path with id=-1 - which the underlying Matter SDKs (iOS ZGMTRAttributeRequestPath/ZGMTREventRequestPath, Android ChipAttributePath/ChipEventPath) treat as nil=wildcard only when the id argument itself is nil/ChipPathId.forWildcard(), not -1. A concrete id of -1 matches no real endpoint/cluster/attribute/event, so the subscription/read silently returns nothing.",
      "fix": "iOS: added pathIdFromJson() helper that returns nil when type==\"wildcard\", used in the subscribe and read handlers' attribute/event path construction. Android: added mapChipPathId() helper that calls ChipPathId.forWildcard() when type==\"wildcard\", used inside mapChipAttributePath()/mapChipEventPath() which both subscribe and read already funnel through.",
      "tags": [
        "ios",
        "android",
        "matter-subscribe",
        "wildcard",
        "native-bridge",
        "chippathid"
      ],
      "related_bugs": [],
      "occurrences": 1,
      "last_seen": "2026-07-20T00:00:00.000Z"
